{"title_page": "2006 in the United States", "text_new": "{{expand list|date=July 2014}}\n{{Yearbox US|2006}}\nEvents from the year '''2006 in the United States'''.\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n== Incumbents ==\n\n=== Federal government ===\n* [[President of the United States|President]]: [[George W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]])\n* [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]: [[Dick Cheney]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Wyoming]])\n* [[Chief Justice of the United States|Chief Justice]]: [[John Roberts]] ([[New York (state)|New York]])<ref>{{cite web|title=John Roberts Biography|url=http://www.biography.com/people/john-roberts-20681147|website=biography.com|publisher=A&E Television Networks|accessdate=28 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives|Speaker of the House of Representatives]]: [[Dennis Hastert]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]&ndash;[[Illinois]])\n* [[Senate Majority Leader]]: [[Bill Frist]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]&ndash;[[Tennessee]])\n* [[United States Congress|Congress]]: [[109th United States Congress|109th]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n! [[Governor (United States)|Governor]]s and [[Lieutenant governor (United States)|lieutenant governor]]s\n|-\n|\n=== Governors ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Governor of Alabama]]: [[Bob Riley]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Alaska]]: [[Frank Murkowski]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until December 4), [[Sarah Palin]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting December 4)\n* [[Governor of Arizona]]: [[Janet Napolitano]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Arkansas]]: [[Mike Huckabee]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of California]]: [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Colorado]]: [[Bill Owens (Colorado politician)|Bill Owens]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Connecticut]]: [[Jodi Rell]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Delaware]]: [[Ruth Ann Minner]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Florida]]: [[Jeb Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Georgia]]: [[Sonny Perdue]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Hawaii]]: [[Linda Lingle]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Idaho]]: [[Dirk Kempthorne]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until May 26), [[Jim Risch]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting May 26) \n* [[Governor of Illinois]]: [[Rod Blagojevich]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Indiana]]: [[Mitch Daniels]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Iowa]]: [[Tom Vilsack]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Kansas]]: [[Kathleen Sebelius]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Kentucky]]: [[Ernie Fletcher]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Louisiana]]: [[Kathleen Blanco]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Maine]]: [[John Baldacci]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Maryland]]: [[Robert L. Ehrlich, Jr.]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Massachusetts]]: [[Mitt Romney]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Michigan]]: [[Jennifer Granholm]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n* [[Governor of Minnesota]]: [[Tim Pawlenty]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Mississippi]]: [[Haley Barbour]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Missouri]]: [[Matt Blunt]] 