/national/04churches.html?scp=1&sq=&st=nyt|title=Fires Destroy 3 Churches and Damage 2 in Alabama|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-03-21|date=February 4, 2006 | first1=Jim | last1=Noles | first2=Campbell | last2=Robertson| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090424225806/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/04/national/04churches.html?scp=1&sq=&st=nyt| archivedate= 24 April 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n* [[February 5]] &ndash; [[Super Bowl XL]]: The [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] defeat the [[Seattle Seahawks]] by a score of 21&ndash;10. It is a homecoming for [[Detroit]] native [[Jerome Bettis]], who was playing the final game of his 12-year career.\n* [[February 9]] &ndash; [[AIG]] apologizes for deceptive business practices and reaches a [[United States dollar|$]]1.64 billion settlement with federal and state securities and insurance regulators.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/10/business/10insure.html?scp=21&sq=&st=nyt|title=A.I.G. Apologizes and Agrees to $1.64 Billion Settlement|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-03-21|date=February 10, 2006 | first=Gretchen | last=Morgenson| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090424230001/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/10/business/10insure.html?scp=21&sq=&st=nyt| archivedate= 24 April 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n* [[February 10]]&ndash;[[February 26]] &ndash; The [[United States at the 2006 Winter Olympics|United States]] compete at the [[2006 Winter Olympics|Winter Olympics]] in [[Turin]], [[Italy]] and win 9 gold, 9 silver, and 7 bronze medals.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}}\n* [[February 11]] &ndash; Vice President [[Dick Cheney]] [[Dick Cheney hunting incident|accidentally shoots and wounds a lawyer]] while quail hunting in southern [[Texas]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/13/politics/13cheney.html?scp=2&sq=&st=nyt|title=Cheney Shoots Fellow Hunter in Mishap on a Texas Ranch|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-03-22|date=February 13, 2006 | first=Anne E. | last=Kornblut| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090424230017/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/13/politics/13cheney.html?scp=2&sq=&st=nyt| archivedate= 24 April 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n* [[February 14]] &ndash; [[The Coca-Cola Company]] says that [[Warren Buffett]], the soft drink maker's largest shareholder, would leave the board in April after 19 years in order to spend more time managing [[Berkshire Hathaway]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/15/business/15coke.html?scp=22&sq=&st=nyt|title=After 17 Years, Buffett to Exit Coke's Board|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-03-28|date=February 15, 2006| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090424230034/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/15/business/15coke.html?scp=22&sq=&st=nyt| archivedate= 24 April 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n* [[February 15]] &ndash; A group of institutional investors already involved in a lawsuit with the company sue [[Tyco International]] to stop its proposed breakup plan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/16/business/16tyco.html?scp=7&sq=&st=nyt|title=Investors Sue Tyco Over Proposed Breakup|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-03-28|date=February 16, 2006| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090424225933/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/02/16/business/16tyco.html?scp=7&sq=&st=nyt| archivedate= 24 April 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref>\n* [[February 16]]\n** The state of [[Minnesota]] sues [[AIG]] for underreporting premiums to reduce its tax bill refusing a settlement of [[United States dollar|$]]1.2 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E03EEDD103EF934A25751C0A9609C8B63&scp=5&sq=&st=nyt|title=Minnesota Sues A.I.G.|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-03-28|date=February 17, 2006}}</ref>\n** The chairman of the [[Federal Reserve]], [[Ben Bernanke]], testifies to the US Senate that Chinese ownership of US assets is not large enough to put the country at risk economically.<ref>{{ci